HEADWORD: Melanochroite
<hw>Mel`a*no*chro"ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Melanochroic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of a red,
or brownish or yellowish red color. It is a chromate of lead; -- called
also <altname>phoenicocroite</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melanocomous</ent>⟦br⟧
